\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 08, 2025</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104fct1665702713420.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fct1665702713420.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fct1665702713420.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"fct1665702713420\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Reference Development Object\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">A Reference Development Object holds the URL of another development object and enables its parent object to access the information in the referenced object. It can be created, modified, and deleted without affecting the object that it references.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fct1665702713420__section_w1342ab1b5b1_w1343ab1b5_w1344ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\"></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fct1665702713420__section_w1345ab1b5b3_w1346ab1b5_w1347ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d861858e56\"> Characteristics </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"fct1665702713420__table_d10460e1_d10461e1_d10462e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"fct1665702713420__table_d10460e1_d10461e1_d10462e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Characteristics</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"fct1665702713420__table_d10460e1_d10461e1_d10462e1__entry__2\"></th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fct1665702713420__table_d10460e1_d10461e1_d10462e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Object type code:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fct1665702713420__table_d10460e1_d10461e1_d10462e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n                            ref</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fct1665702713420__table_d10460e1_d10461e1_d10462e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Icon:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fct1665702713420__table_d10460e1_d10461e1_d10462e1__entry__2\"><img alt=\"Icon\" class=\"image\" id=\"fct1665702713420__image_o5b_nys_4wb\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/reference.png?_LANG=enus\"/>; for example: <img alt=\"Icon\" class=\"image\" id=\"fct1665702713420__image_fnz_4ys_4wb\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/component_reference.png?_LANG=enus\"/> or <img alt=\"Icon\" class=\"image\" id=\"fct1665702713420__image_b23_rys_4wb\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/shell_reference.png?_LANG=enus\"/></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fct1665702713420__table_d10460e1_d10461e1_d10462e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Main Development Object?</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fct1665702713420__table_d10460e1_d10461e1_d10462e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">No</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fct1665702713420__table_d10460e1_d10461e1_d10462e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Part of:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fct1665702713420__table_d10460e1_d10461e1_d10462e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qvi1665702713514.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qvi1665702713514.html\" title=\"A Project is a Main Development Object that defines the contents of an application or part of an application, and is used to control the build process. It is the starting point for all development and contains Reference Development Objects that refer to Main Development Objects.\">Project</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fct1665702713420__table_d10460e1_d10461e1_d10462e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Contains:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fct1665702713420__table_d10460e1_d10461e1_d10462e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jgi1665702550212.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jgi1665702550212.html\" title=\"A Property is a named, typed attribute of Development Object that defines a characteristic or behavior of the object. Each property has a descriptive name, a literal name, a data type, and a value. If no value is specified, a default value may be used.\">Property</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fct1665702713420__table_d10460e1_d10461e1_d10462e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Generalization:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fct1665702713420__table_d10460e1_d10461e1_d10462e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ulo1665702550460.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ulo1665702550460.html\" title=\"A Uniface Development Object is an abstract data type that defines the characteristics and behavior of a logical application unit, such as a Component, Field, Message, Library, and so on.\">Development Object</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fct1665702713420__table_d10460e1_d10461e1_d10462e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Specializations:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fct1665702713420__table_d10460e1_d10461e1_d10462e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">—</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fct1665702713420__table_d10460e1_d10461e1_d10462e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Compilation output</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fct1665702713420__table_d10460e1_d10461e1_d10462e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">—</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fct1665702713420__table_d10460e1_d10461e1_d10462e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">URI format:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fct1665702713420__table_d10460e1_d10461e1_d10462e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">ref:<var class=\"keyword varname\">Name</var>\n</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fct1665702713420__section_w1348ab1b5b5_w1349ab1b5_w1350ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d861858e267\"> Specialization </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fct1665702713420__p_d94610e1_d94611e1_d94612e1\">Reference Development Object specializes Development\n            Object in the following ways:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fct1665702713420__li_d36890e1_d36891e1_d36892e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fct1665702713420__p_d94613e1_d94614e1_d94615e1\">It has a parent object.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fct1665702713420__li_d36893e1_d36894e1_d36895e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fct1665702713420__p_d94616e1_d94617e1_d94618e1\">It cannot have child development objects.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fct1665702713420__li_d36896e1_d36897e1_d36898e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fct1665702713420__p_d94619e1_d94620e1_d94621e1\">It has properties, but does not have code\n                  containers or child objects.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fct1665702713420__li_d36899e1_d36900e1_d36901e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fct1665702713420__p_d94622e1_d94623e1_d94624e1\">It can only be defined in the context of its\n                  parent object. For example, the child objects of a project are reference\n                  development objects.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3612978\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3612978\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Reference Development Object Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 08, 2025 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Reference Development Object A Reference Development Object holds the URL of another development object and enables its parent object to access the information in the referenced object. It can be created, modified, and deleted without affecting the object that it references. Characteristics Characteristics Object type code: ref Icon: ; for example: or Main Development Object? No Part of: Project Contains: Property Generalization: Development Object Specializations: — Compilation output — URI format: ref: Name Specialization Reference Development Object specializes Development Object in the following ways: It has a parent object. It cannot have child development objects. It has properties, but does not have code containers or child objects. It can only be defined in the context of its parent object. For example, the child objects of a project are reference development objects. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}